Intuition
so after looking problem i thought i can solve this problem by using 2 pointers at opposite sides of the array , then i thought how to calculate the area for that i will need difference between the indexes as width and min of left and right pointer i will calculate area then store it and compare it with other areas and keep the max area , to change the pointers , “At each step, the width decreases, so the only way to potentially increase area is by trying to find a larger height, which is why we move the smaller pointer.”

Approach
initalize max_area = 0
initalize left and right pointers
loop condition for opposite pointers(left < right)
calculate width
calculate area
find max area
pointer moving conditions
return max area

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Space complexity:
O(1)
Code
class Solution:
    def maxArea(self, height: List[int]) -> int:
        max_area = 0
        left = 0
        right = len(height) - 1

        while left < right:
            width = right - left
            length = min(height[left], height[right])
            area = width * length
            if area > max_area:
                max_area = area
            if height[left] < height[right]:
                left += 1
            else: 
                right -= 1
        return max_area
